,Recommended,314370,24150611,"Posted: 6 July, 2016",all,Apoch Weiss | Apochs.net,"**QUICK TOUGHTS**Boxlife is a short first person puzzle game in the same vein and stylistic approach as Fancy Skulls, the developer's previous creation. You're thrown into a large room 'Alice in Wonderland' style and are tasked with not only finding four glowing orbs to escape, but also some basic gaming features like jumping and croucing (which is replaced by shrinking), and even flying. The more you discover, the more orbs you find, as well as additional secrets (9 total at the time of writing this) that count towards the game's one and only achievement. It takes about 30 minutes to finish, maybe an hour without a guide (someone posted a completion video is posted in the guide to make it easier). For about a dollar, Boxlife is a decent time waster."
