76561197998975393,Recommended,314370,22547682,"Posted: 21 April, 2016",all,aaronwells,"This is a fun little 3D platformer. It has old-school graphics and no storyline, but it reminded me of a Super Mario 64 level, and I mean that in the best possible way. I loved the spacious feeling of carefully hopping around the narrow high places, and then the claustrophobic feeling of squeezing through tiny funhouse passages.The main downside is that it is a very short game. It took me under an hour to reach the end of the game. (Although there are also apparently 9 ""secrets"" hidden in the map, of which I only found 2, so there's potentially some more play time if you want to hunt those down.) But at least it's cheap."
